    {
      "id": "PopularPost13372",
      "post_content": "Ball lightning is just a great card for any red aggro themed decks. I find it's creature status benefits it quite a bit (as you can't simply [cancel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=cancel) it). However this card isn't without drawbacks. First of all while it's mana cost might be an extremely reasonable (3) it all must be red mana. Where am I getting at? Are you into multicolor decks? You can forget about using ball lightning right on the get go. I'm sure there must be a couple of ways around this however they all require you to be lucky enough to draw the right cards. Another drawback is that, while the creature status might give ball lightning some advantages, it also makes it vulnerable to creature elimination cards (such as [doomblade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=doomblade), sure the name is cliche but the card is brutally effective). This little drawbacks might keep ball lightning from being an unstoppable nightmare, but it is still an excellent source for quick damage. I think all red oriented players should consider ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Fredin",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost13372\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">Ball lightning is just a great card for any red aggro themed decks. I find it's creature status benefits it quite  a bit (as you can't simply <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"cancel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=cancel\">cancel</a> it). However this card isn't without drawbacks. First of all while it's mana cost might be an extremely reasonable (3) it all must be red mana. Where am I getting at? Are you into multicolor decks? You can forget about using ball lightning right on the get go. I'm sure there must be a couple of ways around this however they all require you to be lucky enough to draw the right cards. Another drawback is that, while the creature status might give ball lightning some advantages, it also makes it vulnerable to creature elimination cards (such as <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"doomblade\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=doomblade\">doomblade</a>, sure the name is cliche but the card is brutally effective). This little drawbacks might keep ball lightning from being an unstoppable nightmare, but it is still an excellent source for quick damage. I think all  red oriented players should consider ... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 13372)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '13372'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n      