    {
      "id": "PopularPost15405",
      "post_content": "Fredin, ghostie is right. Also, [Cancel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cancel) is pretty terrible. You should only use it if you can't get a hold of a [Counterspell](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counterspell). I do agree with you though, this card is wonderful - but I do disagree that it needs to be a pure red deck to run it. It really just needs to be primarily red. And there are always things that can tap for both red and another color you decide to run. [Crumbling Necropolis](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crumbling Necropolis) or [Boros Garrison](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Garrison), for example. Also, some non-lands ([Veinfire Borderpost](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Veinfire Borderpost)). Yes, the mana cost tells you that you should be running primarily red - but not **all** red. So yes, please keep these. They're good. =P (Plus, if you rated it a 4/5 in your post - why did you give it a .5/5 on the rating system?)",
      "posted_by": "CeremonialBathory",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost15405\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">Fredin, ghostie is right. Also, <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cancel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cancel\">Cancel</a> is pretty terrible. You should only use it if you can't get a hold of a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Counterspell\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Counterspell\">Counterspell</a>. I do agree with you though, this card is wonderful - but I do disagree that it needs to be a pure red deck to run it. It really just needs to be primarily red. And there are always things that can tap for both red and another color you decide to run. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Crumbling Necropolis\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Crumbling Necropolis\">Crumbling Necropolis</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Boros Garrison\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boros Garrison\">Boros Garrison</a>, for example. Also, some non-lands (<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Veinfire Borderpost\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Veinfire Borderpost\">Veinfire Borderpost</a>). Yes, the mana cost tells you that you should be running primarily red - but not <b>all</b> red. So yes, please keep these. They're good. =P (Plus, if you rated it a 4/5 in your post - why did you give it a .5/5 on the rating system?)</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '15405'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n     